<span class=3D"heading-toc" id=3D"toc-what-is-capital-gains-tax-understandi=
ng-the-basics"></span><h2 id=3D"mntl-sc-block_5-0" class=3D"comp mntl-sc-bl=
ock finance-sc-block-heading mntl-sc-block-heading"> <span class=3D"mntl-sc=
-block-heading__text text-title-300"> What Is Capital Gains Tax? Understand=
ing the Basics </span> </h2>
<p id=3D"mntl-sc-block_6-0" class=3D"comp mntl-sc-block finance-sc-block-ht=
ml mntl-sc-block-html"> Capital gains or profits are referred to as having =
been realized when stock shares or any other taxable investment assets are =
sold. The tax doesn't apply to unsold investments or unrealized capital gai=
ns. Stock shares won't incur taxes until they're sold, no matter how long t=
hey're held or how much they increase in value.
</p>
<div id=3D"mntl-sc-block_7-0" class=3D"comp mntl-sc-block mntl-sc-block-ads=
lot mntl-block"></div>
<p id=3D"mntl-sc-block_8-0" class=3D"comp mntl-sc-block finance-sc-block-ht=
ml mntl-sc-block-html"> The capital gains tax rate applies only to profits =
from the sale of assets held for more than a year, which is referred to as&=
nbsp;<a href=3D"https://www.investopedia.com/articles/personal-finance/1015=
15/comparing-longterm-vs-shortterm-capital-gain-tax-rates.asp" data-compone=
nt=3D"link" data-source=3D"inlineLink" data-type=3D"internalLink" data-ordi=
nal=3D"1">long-term capital gains</a>. The rates are 0%, 15%, or 20% based =
on your annual income bracket, but collectibles are always taxed at 28%.<sp=
an class=3D"mntl-inline-citation mntl-dynamic-tooltip--trigger wrapped" dat=
a-id=3D"#citation-1" tabindex=3D"0"><span>1</span></span>
</p>
<div id=3D"mntl-sc-block_9-0" class=3D"comp mntl-sc-block mntl-sc-block-ads=
lot mntl-block"></div>
<p id=3D"mntl-sc-block_10-0" class=3D"comp mntl-sc-block finance-sc-block-h=
tml mntl-sc-block-html"> Most taxpayers pay a higher rate on their income t=
han on any long-term capital gains they may have realized. That gives them =
a financial incentive to hold investments for at least a year, after which =
the tax on the profit will be lower.
</p>
<div id=3D"mntl-sc-block_11-0" class=3D"comp mntl-sc-block mntl-sc-block-ad=
slot mntl-block"></div>
<div id=3D"mntl-sc-block_12-0" class=3D"comp mntl-sc-block finance-sc-block=
-callout mntl-sc-block-universal-callout theme-important finance-sc-block-c=
allout--generic" data-tracking-id=3D"mntl-sc-block-callout" data-tracking-c=
ontainer=3D"true"> <h3 class=3D"mntl-sc-block-universal-callout__heading">I=
mportant</h3>
<div class=3D"mntl-sc-block-universal-callout__body"><p>Day traders and oth=
ers taking advantage of the ease and speed of trading online should be awar=
e that any profits they make from buying and selling assets held for less t=
han a year aren't just taxed. They're taxed at a higher rate than assets th=
at are held long-term.<span class=3D"mntl-inline-citation mntl-dynamic-tool=
tip--trigger wrapped" data-id=3D"#citation-1" tabindex=3D"0"><span>1</span>=
</span></p></div>
<div id=3D"finance-sc-block-callout__icon-container_1-0" class=3D"comp fina=
nce-sc-block-callout__icon-container mntl-block"><svg class=3D"icon finance=
-sc-block-callout__icon--important ">
<use xmlns:xlink=3D"http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xlink:href=3D"#finance-sc=
-block-callout__icon--important" href=3D"#finance-sc-block-callout__icon--i=
mportant"></use>
</svg></div></div>
<p id=3D"mntl-sc-block_13-0" class=3D"comp mntl-sc-block finance-sc-block-h=
tml mntl-sc-block-html"> An investor will owe long-term capital gains tax o=
n the profits of any investment they've owned for more than one year. <a hr=
ef=3D"https://www.investopedia.com/terms/s/short-term-gain.asp" data-compon=
ent=3D"link" data-source=3D"inlineLink" data-type=3D"internalLink" data-ord=
inal=3D"1">Short-term capital gains</a> apply to assets held for a year or =
less, and are taxed at your <a href=3D"https://www.investopedia.com/terms/o=
/ordinaryincome.asp" data-component=3D"link" data-source=3D"inlineLink" dat=
a-type=3D"internalLink" data-ordinal=3D"2">ordinary income</a>&nbsp;rate. T=
his is usually higher than the long-term capital gains rate for most people=
..<span class=3D"mntl-inline-citation mntl-dynamic-tooltip--trigger wrapped=
" data-id=3D"#citation-1" tabindex=3D"0"><span>1</span></span>
</p>
<div id=3D"mntl-sc-block_14-0" class=3D"comp mntl-sc-block mntl-sc-block-ad=
slot mntl-block"></div>
<span class=3D"heading-toc" id=3D"toc-capital-gains-tax-rates-for-2025"></s=
pan><h2 id=3D"mntl-sc-block_15-0" class=3D"comp mntl-sc-block finance-sc-bl=
ock-heading mntl-sc-block-heading"> <span class=3D"mntl-sc-block-heading__t=
ext text-title-300"> Capital Gains Tax Rates for 2025 </span> </h2>
<p id=3D"mntl-sc-block_16-0" class=3D"comp mntl-sc-block finance-sc-block-h=
tml mntl-sc-block-html"> The profit on an asset that's sold a year or less =
after its purchase is generally treated for tax purposes as if it were wage=
s or salary. Such gains are added to your <a href=3D"https://www.investoped=
ia.com/terms/e/earnedincome.asp" data-component=3D"link" data-source=3D"inl=
ineLink" data-type=3D"internalLink" data-ordinal=3D"1">earned income</a> or=
 ordinary income on your tax return.
</p>
<div id=3D"mntl-sc-block_17-0" class=3D"comp mntl-sc-block mntl-sc-block-ad=
slot mntl-block"></div>
<p id=3D"mntl-sc-block_18-0" class=3D"comp mntl-sc-block finance-sc-block-h=
tml mntl-sc-block-html"> The same generally applies to <a href=3D"https://w=
ww.investopedia.com/terms/d/dividend.asp" data-component=3D"link" data-sour=
ce=3D"inlineLink" data-type=3D"internalLink" data-ordinal=3D"1">dividends</=
a>. They represent profit, although they aren't capital gains. Ordinary div=
idends are taxed as ordinary income. Qualified dividends are subject to the=
 0%, 15%, or 20% capital gains tax.<span class=3D"mntl-inline-citation mntl=
-dynamic-tooltip--trigger wrapped" data-id=3D"#citation-2" tabindex=3D"0"><=
span>2</span></span>
</p>
<div id=3D"mntl-sc-block_19-0" class=3D"comp mntl-sc-block mntl-sc-block-ad=
slot mntl-block"></div>
<p id=3D"mntl-sc-block_20-0" class=3D"comp mntl-sc-block finance-sc-block-h=
tml mntl-sc-block-html"> However, a different system applies to long-term c=
apital gains. The tax you pay on assets held for more than a year and sold =
for a profit varies according to a rate schedule based on your taxable inco=
me. The rates are adjusted annually for <a href=3D"https://www.investopedia=
.com/terms/i/inflation.asp" data-component=3D"link" data-source=3D"inlineLi=
nk" data-type=3D"internalLink" data-ordinal=3D"1">inflation</a>.<span class=
=3D"mntl-inline-citation mntl-dynamic-tooltip--trigger wrapped" data-id=3D"=
#citation-30" tabindex=3D"0"><span>3</span></span>
</p>
<div id=3D"mntl-sc-block_21-0" class=3D"comp mntl-sc-block mntl-sc-block-ad=
slot mntl-block"></div>
<p id=3D"mntl-sc-block_22-0" class=3D"comp mntl-sc-block finance-sc-block-h=
tml mntl-sc-block-html"> The rates for tax year 2025 are shown in this tabl=
e.<span class=3D"mntl-inline-citation mntl-dynamic-tooltip--trigger wrapped=
" data-id=3D"#citation-29" tabindex=3D"0"><span>4</span></span><span class=
=3D"mntl-inline-citation mntl-dynamic-tooltip--trigger wrapped" data-id=3D"=
#citation-37" tabindex=3D"0"><span>5</span></span>
</p>
