<span class=3D"heading-toc" id=3D"toc-capital-gains-tax-exceptions-collecti=
bles-real-estate--investments"></span><h2 id=3D"mntl-sc-block_28-0" class=
=3D"comp mntl-sc-block finance-sc-block-heading mntl-sc-block-heading"> <sp=
an class=3D"mntl-sc-block-heading__text text-title-300"> Capital Gains Tax =
Exceptions: Collectibles, Real Estate, &amp; Investments </span> </h2>
<p id=3D"mntl-sc-block_29-0" class=3D"comp mntl-sc-block finance-sc-block-h=
tml mntl-sc-block-html"> Some categories of assets are subject to different=
 capital gains tax treatment than the norm.
</p>
<div id=3D"mntl-sc-block_30-0" class=3D"comp mntl-sc-block mntl-sc-block-ad=
slot mntl-block"></div>
<h3 id=3D"mntl-sc-block_31-0" class=3D"comp mntl-sc-block finance-sc-block-=
subheading mntl-sc-block-subheading"> <span class=3D"mntl-sc-block-subheadi=
ng__text"> Collectibles </span> </h3>
<p id=3D"mntl-sc-block_32-0" class=3D"comp mntl-sc-block finance-sc-block-h=
tml mntl-sc-block-html"> Short-term gains on&nbsp;<a href=3D"https://www.in=
vestopedia.com/articles/personal-finance/061715/how-are-collectibles-taxed.=
asp" data-component=3D"link" data-source=3D"inlineLink" data-type=3D"intern=
alLink" data-ordinal=3D"1">collectibles,</a>&nbsp;including art, antiques, =
jewelry, precious metals, and stamp collections, are taxed as ordinary inco=
me at graduated tax rates. Net long-term gains on collectibles are taxed wi=
th a cap of 28%.<span class=3D"mntl-inline-citation mntl-dynamic-tooltip--t=
rigger wrapped" data-id=3D"#citation-31" tabindex=3D"0"><span>6</span></spa=
n><span class=3D"mntl-inline-citation mntl-dynamic-tooltip--trigger wrapped=
" data-id=3D"#citation-1" tabindex=3D"0"><span>1</span></span>
</p>
<div id=3D"mntl-sc-block_33-0" class=3D"comp mntl-sc-block mntl-sc-block-ad=
slot mntl-block"></div>
<h3 id=3D"mntl-sc-block_34-0" class=3D"comp mntl-sc-block finance-sc-block-=
subheading mntl-sc-block-subheading"> <span class=3D"mntl-sc-block-subheadi=
ng__text"> Owner-Occupied Real Estate </span> </h3>
<p id=3D"mntl-sc-block_35-0" class=3D"comp mntl-sc-block finance-sc-block-h=
tml mntl-sc-block-html"> A different standard applies to real&nbsp;estate c=
apital gains if you're selling your principal residence. $250,000 of the <a=
 href=3D"https://www.investopedia.com/ask/answers/07/taxtiphome.asp" data-c=
omponent=3D"link" data-source=3D"inlineLink" data-type=3D"internalLink" dat=
a-ordinal=3D"1">capital gains from the sale of your home</a> are excluded f=
rom taxable income. This increases to $500,000 if you are married and filin=
g jointly. You must have owned and lived in the home for two or more years =
during the five years ending on the date of the sale to qualify for this ta=
x break.<span class=3D"mntl-inline-citation mntl-dynamic-tooltip--trigger w=
rapped" data-id=3D"#citation-28" tabindex=3D"0"><span>7</span></span>
</p>
<div id=3D"mntl-sc-block_36-0" class=3D"comp mntl-sc-block mntl-sc-block-ad=
slot mntl-block"></div>
<p id=3D"mntl-sc-block_37-0" class=3D"comp mntl-sc-block finance-sc-block-h=
tml mntl-sc-block-html"> Capital losses from the sale of&nbsp;<a href=3D"ht=
tps://www.investopedia.com/terms/p/personalproperty.asp" data-component=3D"=
link" data-source=3D"inlineLink" data-type=3D"internalLink" data-ordinal=3D=
"1">personal property,</a>&nbsp;such as a home, aren't deductible from gain=
s, however.<span class=3D"mntl-inline-citation mntl-dynamic-tooltip--trigge=
r wrapped" data-id=3D"#citation-5" tabindex=3D"0"><span>8</span></span>
</p>
<div id=3D"mntl-sc-block_38-0" class=3D"comp mntl-sc-block mntl-sc-block-ad=
slot mntl-block"></div>
<p id=3D"mntl-sc-block_39-0" class=3D"comp mntl-sc-block finance-sc-block-h=
tml mntl-sc-block-html"> A single taxpayer who purchased a house for $200,0=
00 and later sells it for $500,000 has made a $300,000 profit on the sale. =
This individual must report a capital gain of $50,000 after applying the $2=
50,000 exemption. This is the amount subject to the capital gains tax.
</p>
<div id=3D"mntl-sc-block_40-0" class=3D"comp mntl-sc-block mntl-sc-block-ad=
slot mntl-block"></div>
<div id=3D"mntl-sc-block_41-0" class=3D"comp mntl-sc-block finance-sc-block=
-callout mntl-sc-block-universal-callout theme-tip finance-sc-block-callout=
--generic" data-tracking-id=3D"mntl-sc-block-callout" data-tracking-contain=
er=3D"true"> <h3 class=3D"mntl-sc-block-universal-callout__heading">Tip</h3=
>
<div class=3D"mntl-sc-block-universal-callout__body"><p>The costs of signif=
icant repairs and improvements to the home can be added to its cost in most=
 cases, reducing the amount of taxable capital gain.<span class=3D"mntl-inl=
ine-citation mntl-dynamic-tooltip--trigger wrapped" data-id=3D"#citation-32=
" tabindex=3D"0"><span>9</span></span></p></div>
<div id=3D"finance-sc-block-callout__icon-container_2-0" class=3D"comp fina=
nce-sc-block-callout__icon-container mntl-block"><svg class=3D"icon finance=
-sc-block-callout__icon--tip ">
<use xmlns:xlink=3D"http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xlink:href=3D"#finance-sc=
-block-callout__icon--tip" href=3D"#finance-sc-block-callout__icon--tip"></=
use>
</svg></div></div>
<h3 id=3D"mntl-sc-block_42-0" class=3D"comp mntl-sc-block finance-sc-block-=
subheading mntl-sc-block-subheading"> <span class=3D"mntl-sc-block-subheadi=
ng__text"> Investment real estate </span> </h3>
<p id=3D"mntl-sc-block_43-0" class=3D"comp mntl-sc-block finance-sc-block-h=
tml mntl-sc-block-html"> Real estate investors can often claim depreciation=
 deductions against income to reflect the steady deterioration of the prope=
rty as it ages.<span class=3D"mntl-inline-citation mntl-dynamic-tooltip--tr=
igger wrapped" data-id=3D"#citation-7" tabindex=3D"0"><span>10</span></span=
> This is a decline in the home's physical condition and isn't related to i=
ts changing value in the real estate market.
</p>
<div id=3D"mntl-sc-block_44-0" class=3D"comp mntl-sc-block mntl-sc-block-ad=
slot mntl-block"></div>
<p id=3D"mntl-sc-block_45-0" class=3D"comp mntl-sc-block finance-sc-block-h=
tml mntl-sc-block-html"> The depreciation deduction effectively reduces the=
 amount you have paid for the property. That can, in turn, increase your ta=
xable capital gain if you sell because the gap between the property's value=
 after deductions and its sale price will be greater.
</p>
<div id=3D"mntl-sc-block_46-0" class=3D"comp mntl-sc-block mntl-sc-block-ad=
slot mntl-block"></div>
<p id=3D"mntl-sc-block_47-0" class=3D"comp mntl-sc-block finance-sc-block-h=
tml mntl-sc-block-html"> If you paid $100,000 for the building, you'd be ta=
xed as if you'd paid $95,000. You're permitted to claim $5,000 in depreciat=
ion, which is then treated as&nbsp;a recapture of those depreciation deduct=
ions at the time of sale.
</p>
<div id=3D"mntl-sc-block_48-0" class=3D"comp mntl-sc-block mntl-sc-block-ad=
slot mntl-block"></div>
<p id=3D"mntl-sc-block_49-0" class=3D"comp mntl-sc-block finance-sc-block-h=
tml mntl-sc-block-html"> The tax rate that applies to the recaptured amount=
 is 25%, so there would be total capital gains of $15,000 if you then sold =
the building for $110,000. Then, $5,000 of the sale figure would be treated=
 as a recapture of the deduction from income. That recaptured amount is tax=
ed at 25%. The remaining $10,000 of capital gain would be taxed at 0%, 15%,=
 or 20%, depending on the investor's income.<span class=3D"mntl-inline-cita=
tion mntl-dynamic-tooltip--trigger wrapped" data-id=3D"#citation-31" tabind=
ex=3D"0"><span>6</span></span>
</p>
<div id=3D"mntl-sc-block_50-0" class=3D"comp mntl-sc-block mntl-sc-block-ad=
slot mntl-block"></div>
<h3 id=3D"mntl-sc-block_51-0" class=3D"comp mntl-sc-block finance-sc-block-=
subheading mntl-sc-block-subheading"> <span class=3D"mntl-sc-block-subheadi=
ng__text"> Investment Exceptions </span> </h3>
<p id=3D"mntl-sc-block_52-0" class=3D"comp mntl-sc-block finance-sc-block-h=
tml mntl-sc-block-html"> You may be subject to the net investment income ta=
x if you have a high income. This tax imposes an additional 3.8% on your in=
vestment income, including your capital gains, if your <a href=3D"https://w=
ww.investopedia.com/terms/m/magi.asp" data-component=3D"link" data-source=
=3D"inlineLink" data-type=3D"internalLink" data-ordinal=3D"1">modified adju=
sted gross income (MAGI)</a> exceeds certain maximums.
</p>
<div id=3D"mntl-sc-block_53-0" class=3D"comp mntl-sc-block mntl-sc-block-ad=
slot mntl-block"></div>
<p id=3D"mntl-sc-block_54-0" class=3D"comp mntl-sc-block finance-sc-block-h=
tml mntl-sc-block-html"> The threshold amount is $250,000 if you're married=
 and filing jointly or you're a surviving spouse as of 2025. It's $200,000 =
if you=E2=80=99re single or a head of household and $125,000 if you're marr=
ied and filing a separate return.<span class=3D"mntl-inline-citation mntl-d=
ynamic-tooltip--trigger wrapped" data-id=3D"#citation-23" tabindex=3D"0"><s=
pan>11</span></span>
</p>
<div id=3D"mntl-sc-block_55-0" class=3D"comp mntl-sc-block mntl-sc-block-ad=
slot mntl-block"></div>
<span class=3D"heading-toc" id=3D"toc-calculating-your-capital-gains"></spa=
n><h2 id=3D"mntl-sc-block_56-0" class=3D"comp mntl-sc-block finance-sc-bloc=
k-heading mntl-sc-block-heading"> <span class=3D"mntl-sc-block-heading__tex=
t text-title-300"> Calculating Your Capital Gains </span> </h2>
<p id=3D"mntl-sc-block_57-0" class=3D"comp mntl-sc-block finance-sc-block-h=
tml mntl-sc-block-html"> Capital losses can be deducted from capital gains =
to calculate your taxable gains for the year. The calculation becomes a lit=
tle more complex, however, if you've incurred capital gains and capital los=
ses on both short-term and long-term investments.
</p>
<div id=3D"mntl-sc-block_58-0" class=3D"comp mntl-sc-block mntl-sc-block-ad=
slot mntl-block"></div>
<p id=3D"mntl-sc-block_59-0" class=3D"comp mntl-sc-block finance-sc-block-h=
tml mntl-sc-block-html"> First, sort short-term gains and losses into a sep=
arate pile from long-term gains and losses. All short-term gains must be re=
conciled to yield a total short-term gain, and then the short-term losses a=
re totaled. Finally, long-term gains and losses are tallied.
</p>
<div id=3D"mntl-sc-block_60-0" class=3D"comp mntl-sc-block mntl-sc-block-ad=
slot mntl-block"></div>
<p id=3D"mntl-sc-block_61-0" class=3D"comp mntl-sc-block finance-sc-block-h=
tml mntl-sc-block-html"> Short-term gains are netted against short-term los=
ses to produce a net short-term gain or loss. The same is done with long-te=
rm gains and losses.<span class=3D"mntl-inline-citation mntl-dynamic-toolti=
p--trigger wrapped" data-id=3D"#citation-9" tabindex=3D"0"><span>12</span><=
/span>
</p>
<div id=3D"mntl-sc-block_62-0" class=3D"comp mntl-sc-block mntl-sc-block-ad=
slot mntl-block"></div>
<div id=3D"mntl-sc-block_63-0" class=3D"comp mntl-sc-block finance-sc-block=
-callout mntl-sc-block-universal-callout theme-tip finance-sc-block-callout=
--generic" data-tracking-id=3D"mntl-sc-block-callout" data-tracking-contain=
er=3D"true"> <h3 class=3D"mntl-sc-block-universal-callout__heading">Tip</h3=
>
<div class=3D"mntl-sc-block-universal-callout__body"><p>Many individuals ca=
lculate their tax obligations using <a href=3D"https://www.investopedia.com=
/the-best-tax-software-8780098" data-component=3D"link" data-source=3D"inli=
neLink" data-type=3D"internalLink" data-ordinal=3D"1">software</a> that aut=
omatically makes the computations. You can use a capital gains calculator t=
o get a rough idea of what you may pay on a potential or actualized sale.</=
p></div>
<div id=3D"finance-sc-block-callout__icon-container_3-0" class=3D"comp fina=
nce-sc-block-callout__icon-container mntl-block"><svg class=3D"icon finance=
-sc-block-callout__icon--tip ">
<use xmlns:xlink=3D"http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xlink:href=3D"#finance-sc=
-block-callout__icon--tip" href=3D"#finance-sc-block-callout__icon--tip"></=
use>
</svg></div></div>
<span class=3D"heading-toc" id=3D"toc-how-to-reduce-capital-gains-tax-legal=
ly"></span><h2 id=3D"mntl-sc-block_64-0" class=3D"comp mntl-sc-block financ=
e-sc-block-heading mntl-sc-block-heading"> <span class=3D"mntl-sc-block-hea=
ding__text text-title-300"> How to Reduce Capital Gains Tax Legally </span>=
 </h2>
<p id=3D"mntl-sc-block_65-0" class=3D"comp mntl-sc-block finance-sc-block-h=
tml mntl-sc-block-html"> You'll owe capital gains tax on the profit if you =
want to invest money and make money. You can <a href=3D"https://www.investo=
pedia.com/how-to-be-a-tax-efficient-investor-8414283" data-component=3D"lin=
k" data-source=3D"inlineLink" data-type=3D"internalLink" data-ordinal=3D"1"=
>minimize your capital gains taxes</a> in several ways, however.<br>
</p>
<div id=3D"mntl-sc-block_66-0" class=3D"comp mntl-sc-block mntl-sc-block-ad=
slot mntl-block"></div>
<ul id=3D"mntl-sc-block_67-0" class=3D"comp mntl-sc-block finance-sc-block-=
html mntl-sc-block-html">
<li>Hold your investment for more than one year. Otherwise, the profit will=
 be treated as regular income, and you'll most likely pay more.<span class=
=3D"mntl-inline-citation mntl-dynamic-tooltip--trigger wrapped" data-id=3D"=
#citation-1" tabindex=3D"0"><span>1</span></span></li>
<li>Don't forget that your investment losses can be deducted from your inve=
stment profits. You can claim $3,000 in losses a year. Some investors use t=
his benefit to good effect. They'll sell a loser at the end of the year, so=
 they have losses to offset their gains for the year. You can carry the exc=
ess losses forward and deduct them from your capital gains in future years =
if your losses are greater than $3,000.<span class=3D"mntl-inline-citation =
mntl-dynamic-tooltip--trigger wrapped" data-id=3D"#citation-33" tabindex=3D=
"0"><span>13</span></span></li>
<li>Keep track of any qualifying expenses you incur in making or maintainin=
g your investment. These expenses will increase the cost basis of the inves=
tment and reduce its taxable profit.</li>
<li>Be mindful of <a href=3D"https://www.investopedia.com/terms/t/tax-advan=
taged.asp" data-component=3D"link" data-source=3D"inlineLink" data-type=3D"=
internalLink" data-ordinal=3D"1">tax-advantaged</a> accounts. Holding secur=
ities in a 401(k) or IRA can limit the <a href=3D"https://www.investopedia.=
com/terms/l/liquidity.asp" data-component=3D"link" data-source=3D"inlineLin=
k" data-type=3D"internalLink" data-ordinal=3D"2">liquidity</a> you have in =
your investment and your options to withdraw funds. However, you may have g=
reater capabilities in buying and selling securities without incurring taxe=
s on gains.</li><span class=3D"mntl-sc-block-adslot mntl-sc-block-adslot-in=
line"></span>
<li>Seek out exclusions. If you want to sell your house, ensure that you un=
derstand the rules that allow you to exclude a portion of gains from the sa=
le. If possible, intentionally meet the criteria to plan the timing of the =
sale and ensure that you meet exclusion requirements.</li>
</ul>
<div id=3D"mntl-sc-block_68-0" class=3D"comp mntl-sc-block mntl-sc-block-ad=
slot mntl-block"></div>
<span class=3D"heading-toc" id=3D"toc-capital-gains-tax-strategies"></span>=
<h2 id=3D"mntl-sc-block_69-0" class=3D"comp mntl-sc-block finance-sc-block-=
heading mntl-sc-block-heading"> <span class=3D"mntl-sc-block-heading__text =
text-title-300"> Capital Gains Tax Strategies </span> </h2>
<p id=3D"mntl-sc-block_70-0" class=3D"comp mntl-sc-block finance-sc-block-h=
tml mntl-sc-block-html"> The capital gains tax effectively reduces the over=
all return generated by an investment, but there are legitimate ways to red=
uce or even eliminate net capital gains taxes for the year.
</p>
<div id=3D"mntl-sc-block_71-0" class=3D"comp mntl-sc-block mntl-sc-block-ad=
slot mntl-block"></div>
<p id=3D"mntl-sc-block_72-0" class=3D"comp mntl-sc-block finance-sc-block-h=
tml mntl-sc-block-html"> The simplest strategy is to hold assets for more t=
han a year before selling them. The tax you'll pay on long-term capital gai=
ns is generally lower than it would be for short-term gains.<span class=3D"=
mntl-inline-citation mntl-dynamic-tooltip--trigger wrapped" data-id=3D"#cit=
ation-1" tabindex=3D"0"><span>1</span></span>
</p>
<div id=3D"mntl-sc-block_73-0" class=3D"comp mntl-sc-block mntl-sc-block-ad=
slot mntl-block"></div>
<h3 id=3D"mntl-sc-block_74-0" class=3D"comp mntl-sc-block finance-sc-block-=
subheading mntl-sc-block-subheading"> <span class=3D"mntl-sc-block-subheadi=
ng__text"> Capital Losses and Tax-Loss Harvesting </span> </h3>
<p id=3D"mntl-sc-block_75-0" class=3D"comp mntl-sc-block finance-sc-block-h=
tml mntl-sc-block-html"> Capital losses will offset capital gains and effec=
tively lower your capital gains tax for the year, but what if the losses ar=
e greater than the gains?
</p>
<div id=3D"mntl-sc-block_76-0" class=3D"comp mntl-sc-block mntl-sc-block-ad=
slot mntl-block"></div>
<p id=3D"mntl-sc-block_77-0" class=3D"comp mntl-sc-block finance-sc-block-h=
tml mntl-sc-block-html"> You can claim the amount against your income if yo=
ur losses exceed your gains by up to $3,000. The loss rolls over, so any ex=
cess unused loss above $3,000 in the current year can be deducted from inco=
me to reduce your tax liability in future years.<span class=3D"mntl-inline-=
citation mntl-dynamic-tooltip--trigger wrapped" data-id=3D"#citation-33" ta=
bindex=3D"0"><span>13</span></span>
</p>
<div id=3D"mntl-sc-block_78-0" class=3D"comp mntl-sc-block mntl-sc-block-ad=
slot mntl-block"></div>
<p id=3D"mntl-sc-block_79-0" class=3D"comp mntl-sc-block finance-sc-block-h=
tml mntl-sc-block-html"> Say an <a href=3D"https://www.investopedia.com/bes=
t-online-brokers-4587872" data-component=3D"link" data-source=3D"inlineLink=
" data-type=3D"internalLink" data-ordinal=3D"1">investor</a> realizes a pro=
fit of $5,000 from selling some stocks but incurs a loss of $20,000 from se=
lling others. The capital loss can be used to cancel out tax liability for =
the $5,000 gain. The remaining capital loss of $15,000 can then be used to =
offset income and the tax on those earnings.
</p>
<div id=3D"mntl-sc-block_80-0" class=3D"comp mntl-sc-block mntl-sc-block-ad=
slot mntl-block"></div>
<p id=3D"mntl-sc-block_81-0" class=3D"comp mntl-sc-block finance-sc-block-h=
tml mntl-sc-block-html"> The <a href=3D"https://www.investopedia.com/the-be=
st-robo-advisors-8764849" data-component=3D"link" data-source=3D"inlineLink=
" data-type=3D"internalLink" data-ordinal=3D"1">investor</a> whose annual i=
nvestment income is $50,000 would report $50,000 minus a yearly maximum cla=
im of $3,000 in the first year. That leaves a total of $47,000 in taxable i=
ncome. The investor still has $12,000 in capital losses and can deduct the =
$3,000 maximum yearly for the next four years.
</p>
<div id=3D"mntl-sc-block_82-0" class=3D"comp mntl-sc-block mntl-sc-block-ad=
slot mntl-block"></div>
<h3 id=3D"mntl-sc-block_83-0" class=3D"comp mntl-sc-block finance-sc-block-=
subheading mntl-sc-block-subheading"> <span class=3D"mntl-sc-block-subheadi=
ng__text"> Don't Break the Wash Sale Rule </span> </h3>
<p id=3D"mntl-sc-block_84-0" class=3D"comp mntl-sc-block finance-sc-block-h=
tml mntl-sc-block-html"> Be mindful of selling stock shares at a loss to ge=
t a tax advantage and then turning around and buying the same investment ag=
ain. You'll run afoul of the IRS&nbsp;<a href=3D"https://www.investopedia.c=
om/terms/w/washsale.asp" data-component=3D"link" data-source=3D"inlineLink"=
 data-type=3D"internalLink" data-ordinal=3D"1">wash sale rule</a> against t=
his sequence of transactions if you do it within 30 days or less.<span clas=
s=3D"mntl-inline-citation mntl-dynamic-tooltip--trigger wrapped" data-id=3D=
"#citation-11" tabindex=3D"0"><span>14</span></span>
</p>
<div id=3D"mntl-sc-block_85-0" class=3D"comp mntl-sc-block mntl-sc-block-ad=
slot mntl-block"></div>
<p id=3D"mntl-sc-block_86-0" class=3D"comp mntl-sc-block finance-sc-block-h=
tml mntl-sc-block-html"> Material capital gains of any kind are reported on=
 a&nbsp;<a href=3D"https://www.investopedia.com/terms/s/scheduled.asp" data=
-component=3D"link" data-source=3D"inlineLink" data-type=3D"internalLink" d=
ata-ordinal=3D"1">Schedule D form</a>.<span class=3D"mntl-inline-citation m=
ntl-dynamic-tooltip--trigger wrapped" data-id=3D"#citation-12" tabindex=3D"=
0"><span>15</span></span>
</p>
<div id=3D"mntl-sc-block_87-0" class=3D"comp mntl-sc-block mntl-sc-block-ad=
slot mntl-block"></div>
<h3 id=3D"mntl-sc-block_88-0" class=3D"comp mntl-sc-block finance-sc-block-=
subheading mntl-sc-block-subheading"> <span class=3D"mntl-sc-block-subheadi=
ng__text"> Use Tax-Advantaged Retirement Plans </span> </h3>
<p id=3D"mntl-sc-block_89-0" class=3D"comp mntl-sc-block finance-sc-block-h=
tml mntl-sc-block-html"> Among the many reasons to participate in a retirem=
ent plan like a <a href=3D"https://www.investopedia.com/terms/1/401kplan.as=
p" data-component=3D"link" data-source=3D"inlineLink" data-type=3D"internal=
Link" data-ordinal=3D"1">401(k)</a> or an <a href=3D"https://www.investoped=
ia.com/terms/i/ira.asp" data-component=3D"link" data-source=3D"inlineLink" =
data-type=3D"internalLink" data-ordinal=3D"2">individual retirement account=
 (IRA)</a> is that your investments grow from year to year without being su=
bject to capital gains tax. You can buy and sell within a retirement plan w=
ithout paying taxes every year.
</p>
<div id=3D"mntl-sc-block_90-0" class=3D"comp mntl-sc-block mntl-sc-block-ad=
slot mntl-block"></div>
<p id=3D"mntl-sc-block_91-0" class=3D"comp mntl-sc-block finance-sc-block-h=
tml mntl-sc-block-html"> Most traditional tax-advantaged retirement plans d=
on't require participants to pay tax on the funds until they're withdrawn f=
rom the plan. Withdrawals are taxed as ordinary income regardless of the un=
derlying investment.<span class=3D"mntl-inline-citation mntl-dynamic-toolti=
p--trigger wrapped" data-id=3D"#citation-34" tabindex=3D"0"><span>16</span>=
</span>
</p>
<div id=3D"mntl-sc-block_92-0" class=3D"comp mntl-sc-block mntl-sc-block-ad=
slot mntl-block"></div>
<div id=3D"mntl-sc-block_93-0" class=3D"comp mntl-sc-block finance-sc-block=
-callout mntl-sc-block-universal-callout theme-important finance-sc-block-c=
allout--generic" data-tracking-id=3D"mntl-sc-block-callout" data-tracking-c=
ontainer=3D"true"> <h3 class=3D"mntl-sc-block-universal-callout__heading">I=
mportant</h3>
<div class=3D"mntl-sc-block-universal-callout__body"><p>Qualified withdrawa=
ls from a Roth IRA or Roth 401(k) are tax-free if it's been five years sinc=
e you first contributed to the account. Income taxes for these contribution=
s are collected as you pay money into the account.<span class=3D"mntl-inlin=
e-citation mntl-dynamic-tooltip--trigger wrapped" data-id=3D"#citation-34" =
tabindex=3D"0"><span>16</span></span><br></p></div>
<div id=3D"finance-sc-block-callout__icon-container_4-0" class=3D"comp fina=
nce-sc-block-callout__icon-container mntl-block"><svg class=3D"icon finance=
-sc-block-callout__icon--important ">
<use xmlns:xlink=3D"http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xlink:href=3D"#finance-sc=
-block-callout__icon--important" href=3D"#finance-sc-block-callout__icon--i=
mportant"></use>
</svg></div></div>
<h3 id=3D"mntl-sc-block_94-0" class=3D"comp mntl-sc-block finance-sc-block-=
subheading mntl-sc-block-subheading"> <span class=3D"mntl-sc-block-subheadi=
ng__text"> Cash in After Retiring&nbsp; </span> </h3>
<p id=3D"mntl-sc-block_95-0" class=3D"comp mntl-sc-block finance-sc-block-h=
tml mntl-sc-block-html"> Consider waiting until you stop working to sell pr=
ofitable assets. The capital gains tax bill might be reduced if your retire=
ment income is lower. You may even be able to avoid having to pay capital g=
ains tax at all.
</p>
<div id=3D"mntl-sc-block_96-0" class=3D"comp mntl-sc-block mntl-sc-block-ad=
slot mntl-block"></div>
<p id=3D"mntl-sc-block_97-0" class=3D"comp mntl-sc-block finance-sc-block-h=
tml mntl-sc-block-html"> Be mindful of the impact of taking the tax hit whi=
le you're working rather than after you've retired. Realizing the gain earl=
ier might serve to bump you out of a low- or no-pay bracket and cause you t=
o incur a tax bill on the gains.
</p>
<div id=3D"mntl-sc-block_98-0" class=3D"comp mntl-sc-block mntl-sc-block-ad=
slot mntl-block"></div>
<h3 id=3D"mntl-sc-block_99-0" class=3D"comp mntl-sc-block finance-sc-block-=
subheading mntl-sc-block-subheading"> <span class=3D"mntl-sc-block-subheadi=
ng__text"> Watch Your Holding Periods </span> </h3>
<p id=3D"mntl-sc-block_100-0" class=3D"comp mntl-sc-block finance-sc-block-=
html mntl-sc-block-html"> Remember that an asset must be sold at least a ye=
ar or more after it was purchased for the sale to qualify for treatment as =
a long-term capital gain.<span class=3D"mntl-inline-citation mntl-dynamic-t=
ooltip--trigger wrapped" data-id=3D"#citation-1" tabindex=3D"0"><span>1</sp=
an></span> Be sure to check the actual trade date of the purchase before yo=
u sell if you're selling a security that you bought about a year ago. You m=
ight be able to avoid its treatment as a short-term capital gain by waiting=
 only a few days.
</p>
<div id=3D"mntl-sc-block_101-0" class=3D"comp mntl-sc-block mntl-sc-block-a=
dslot mntl-block"></div>
<p id=3D"mntl-sc-block_102-0" class=3D"comp mntl-sc-block finance-sc-block-=
html mntl-sc-block-html"> These timing maneuvers matter more with large tra=
des than small ones.
</p>
<div id=3D"mntl-sc-block_103-0" class=3D"comp mntl-sc-block mntl-sc-block-a=
dslot mntl-block"></div>
<h3 id=3D"mntl-sc-block_104-0" class=3D"comp mntl-sc-block finance-sc-block=
-subheading mntl-sc-block-subheading"> <span class=3D"mntl-sc-block-subhead=
ing__text"> Choose Your Basis&nbsp; </span> </h3>
<p id=3D"mntl-sc-block_105-0" class=3D"comp mntl-sc-block finance-sc-block-=
html mntl-sc-block-html"> Most investors use the&nbsp;<a href=3D"https://ww=
w.investopedia.com/terms/f/fifo.asp" data-component=3D"link" data-source=3D=
"inlineLink" data-type=3D"internalLink" data-ordinal=3D"1">first-in, first-=
out (FIFO)</a> method to calculate the cost basis when they acquire and sel=
l shares in the same company or mutual fund at different times. However, th=
ere are four other methods to choose from:&nbsp;<a href=3D"https://www.inve=
stopedia.com/terms/l/lifo.asp" data-component=3D"link" data-source=3D"inlin=
eLink" data-type=3D"internalLink" data-ordinal=3D"2">last in, first out (LI=
FO)</a>,&nbsp;<a href=3D"https://www.investopedia.com/terms/d/dollar-value-=
lifo.asp" data-component=3D"link" data-source=3D"inlineLink" data-type=3D"i=
nternalLink" data-ordinal=3D"3">dollar value LIFO</a>,&nbsp;<a href=3D"http=
s://www.investopedia.com/terms/a/averagecostmethod.asp" data-component=3D"l=
ink" data-source=3D"inlineLink" data-type=3D"internalLink" data-ordinal=3D"=
4">average cost</a>, and&nbsp;<a href=3D"https://www.investopedia.com/terms=
/s/specific-share-identification.asp" data-component=3D"link" data-source=
=3D"inlineLink" data-type=3D"internalLink" data-ordinal=3D"5">specific shar=
e identification</a>.<span class=3D"mntl-inline-citation mntl-dynamic-toolt=
ip--trigger wrapped" data-id=3D"#citation-36" tabindex=3D"0"><span>17</span=
></span> Average cost is only available for <a href=3D"https://www.investop=
edia.com/terms/a/averagecostbasismethod.asp" data-component=3D"link" data-s=
ource=3D"inlineLink" data-type=3D"internalLink" data-ordinal=3D"6">mutual f=
und shares</a>.
</p>
<div id=3D"mntl-sc-block_106-0" class=3D"comp mntl-sc-block mntl-sc-block-a=
dslot mntl-block"></div>
<p id=3D"mntl-sc-block_107-0" class=3D"comp mntl-sc-block finance-sc-block-=
html mntl-sc-block-html"> Your best choice will depend on several factors, =
such as the basis price of shares or units purchased and the amount of gain=
 that will be declared. For complex cases, you may want to consult with a t=
ax advisor.
</p>
<div id=3D"mntl-sc-block_108-0" class=3D"comp mntl-sc-block mntl-sc-block-a=
dslot mntl-block"></div>
<p id=3D"mntl-sc-block_109-0" class=3D"comp mntl-sc-block finance-sc-block-=
html mntl-sc-block-html"> Computing your cost basis can be a tricky proposi=
tion. Your statements will be on its website if you use an online broker. B=
e sure you have accurate records in some form in any case.
</p>
<div id=3D"mntl-sc-block_110-0" class=3D"comp mntl-sc-block mntl-sc-block-a=
dslot mntl-block"></div>
<p id=3D"mntl-sc-block_111-0" class=3D"comp mntl-sc-block finance-sc-block-=
html mntl-sc-block-html"> Determining when a security was purchased and at =
what price can be a nightmare if you've lost the original confirmation stat=
ement or other records. This is especially troublesome if you have to deter=
mine precisely how much was gained or lost when you're selling a stock, so =
be sure to keep track of your statements. You'll need those dates for the S=
chedule D form.<br>
</p>
<div id=3D"mntl-sc-block_112-0" class=3D"comp mntl-sc-block mntl-sc-block-a=
dslot mntl-block"></div>
<div id=3D"mntl-sc-block_113-0" class=3D"comp mntl-sc-block finance-sc-bloc=
k-questionandanswer mntl-sc-block-questionandanswer"><span class=3D"heading=
-toc" id=3D"toc-what-are-capital-gain-taxes"></span> <h2 class=3D"mntl-sc-b=
lock-questionandanswer__question">What Are Capital Gain Taxes?</h2>
<div class=3D"mntl-sc-block-questionandanswer__answer"><p>Capital gain taxe=
s are taxes imposed on the profit of the sale of an asset. The capital gain=
s tax rate will vary by taxpayer based on the holding period of the asset, =
the taxpayer's income level, and the nature of the asset that was sold.</p>=
</div>
</div>
<div id=3D"mntl-sc-block_114-0" class=3D"comp mntl-sc-block mntl-sc-block-a=
dslot mntl-block"></div>
<div id=3D"mntl-sc-block_115-0" class=3D"comp mntl-sc-block finance-sc-bloc=
k-questionandanswer mntl-sc-block-questionandanswer"><span class=3D"heading=
-toc" id=3D"toc-when-do-you-owe-capital-gains-taxes"></span> <h2 class=3D"m=
ntl-sc-block-questionandanswer__question">When Do You Owe Capital Gains Tax=
es?</h2>
<div class=3D"mntl-sc-block-questionandanswer__answer"><p>You'll owe the ta=
x on capital gains for the tax year in which you realize the gain. Long-ter=
m capital gains taxes are owed on profits from the sale of most investments=
 if they're held for longer than one year. The profits are considered short=
-term gains and are taxed as ordinary income if they're held for one year o=
r less. This is a higher tax rate for most people.<span class=3D"mntl-inlin=
e-citation mntl-dynamic-tooltip--trigger wrapped" data-id=3D"#citation-1" t=
abindex=3D"0"><span>1</span></span></p></div>
</div>
<div id=3D"mntl-sc-block_116-0" class=3D"comp mntl-sc-block mntl-sc-block-a=
dslot mntl-block"></div>
<div id=3D"mntl-sc-block_117-0" class=3D"comp mntl-sc-block finance-sc-bloc=
k-questionandanswer mntl-sc-block-questionandanswer"><span class=3D"heading=
-toc" id=3D"toc-do-i-have-to-pay-capital-gains-taxes-immediately"></span> <=
h2 class=3D"mntl-sc-block-questionandanswer__question">Do I Have to Pay Cap=
ital Gains Taxes Immediately?</h2>
<div class=3D"mntl-sc-block-questionandanswer__answer"><p>You must pay the =
capital gains tax after you sell an asset in most cases. The IRS may requir=
e quarterly estimated tax payments in some cases.<span class=3D"mntl-inline=
-citation mntl-dynamic-tooltip--trigger wrapped" data-id=3D"#citation-1" ta=
bindex=3D"0"><span>1</span></span> The actual tax may not be due for a whil=
e but you may incur penalties for having a large payment due without having=
 made any installment payments toward it.<span class=3D"mntl-inline-citatio=
n mntl-dynamic-tooltip--trigger wrapped" data-id=3D"#citation-35" tabindex=
=3D"0"><span>18</span></span><br></p></div>
</div>
<div id=3D"mntl-sc-block_118-0" class=3D"comp mntl-sc-block mntl-sc-block-a=
dslot mntl-block"></div>
<div id=3D"mntl-sc-block_119-0" class=3D"comp mntl-sc-block finance-sc-bloc=
k-questionandanswer mntl-sc-block-questionandanswer"><span class=3D"heading=
-toc" id=3D"toc-are-there-capital-gains-tax-exemptions-on-home-sales"></spa=
n> <h2 class=3D"mntl-sc-block-questionandanswer__question">Are There Capita=
l Gains Tax Exemptions on Home Sales?</h2>
<div class=3D"mntl-sc-block-questionandanswer__answer"><p>Yes. If the home =
is your primary residence, married couples can exclude up to $500,000 (sing=
les up to $250,000), provided you lived there for two of the last five year=
s.<span class=3D"mntl-inline-citation mntl-dynamic-tooltip--trigger wrapped=
" data-id=3D"#citation-28" tabindex=3D"0"><span>7</span></span></p></div>
</div>
<div id=3D"mntl-sc-block_120-0" class=3D"comp mntl-sc-block mntl-sc-block-a=
dslot mntl-block"></div>
<span class=3D"heading-toc" id=3D"toc-the-bottom-line"></span><h2 id=3D"mnt=
l-sc-block_121-0" class=3D"comp mntl-sc-block finance-sc-block-heading mntl=
-sc-block-heading"> <span class=3D"mntl-sc-block-heading__text text-title-3=
00"> The Bottom Line </span> </h2>
<p id=3D"mntl-sc-block_122-0" class=3D"comp mntl-sc-block finance-sc-block-=
html mntl-sc-block-html"> Capital gains taxes are levied on profits made fr=
om the sale of assets like stocks or <a href=3D"https://www.investopedia.co=
m/terms/r/realestate.asp" data-component=3D"link" data-source=3D"inlineLink=
" data-type=3D"internalLink" data-ordinal=3D"1">real estate</a>. The tax is=
 based on the holding term and the taxpayer's income level and is computed =
using the difference between the asset's sale price and its acquisition pri=
ce. It can be subject to different rates.
</p></div>
<div id=3D"mm-ads-textnote_1-0" class=3D"comp mm-ads-textnote mm-ads-gpt-ad=
unit textnote-placeholder gpt textnote ">
<div id=3D"textnote" class=3D"wrapper"></div>
</div></div>
</div><div class=3D"loc article-post-content"><div id=3D"article-sources_1-=
0" class=3D"comp article-sources mntl-article-sources mntl-expandable-block=
" data-scroll-offset=3D"100"><div class=3D"loc toggle-content"><div id=3D"m=
ntl-article-sources__wrapper_1-0" class=3D"comp mntl-article-sources__wrapp=
er mntl-block article-sources__wrapper" data-click-tracked=3D"true"><div id=
=3D"mntl-article-sources__heading_1-0" class=3D"comp mntl-article-sources__=
heading mntl-text-block article-sources__heading">Article Sources</div>
<div id=3D"mntl-article-sources__icon-wrapper_1-0" class=3D"comp mntl-artic=
